1
00:00:01,500 --> 00:00:04,716
In Verona there are two families.

2
00:00:05,516 --> 00:00:08,492
The Montagues and the Capulets.

3
00:00:09,292 --> 00:00:12,316
The two families hate each other.

4
00:00:13,116 --> 00:00:15,900
Romeo is a Montague.

5
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:19,340
He is a young man.

6
00:00:20,140 --> 00:00:23,116
Juliet is a Capulet.

7
00:00:23,916 --> 00:00:26,628
She is a beautiful girl.

8
00:00:27,428 --> 00:00:31,532
One evening, there is a party at the Capulet house.

9
00:00:32,332 --> 00:00:34,972
Romeo goes to the party.

10
00:00:35,772 --> 00:00:40,356
He must not go. He is a Montague.

11
00:00:41,156 --> 00:00:43,532
But he goes anyway.

12
00:00:44,332 --> 00:00:48,076
At the party, Romeo sees Juliet.

13
00:00:48,876 --> 00:00:52,644
"Who is that girl?" asks Romeo.

14
00:00:53,444 --> 00:00:57,548
"She is the daughter of the Capulets," says his friend.

15
00:00:58,348 --> 00:01:01,036
Romeo does not listen.

16
00:01:01,836 --> 00:01:04,812
He goes to Juliet and speaks to her.

17
00:01:05,612 --> 00:01:08,372
They look into each other's eyes.

18
00:01:09,172 --> 00:01:11,140
It is love.

19
00:01:11,940 --> 00:01:16,764
That night, Romeo goes under Juliet's balcony.

20
00:01:17,564 --> 00:01:20,516
Juliet is on the balcony.

21
00:01:21,316 --> 00:01:24,748
She looks at the stars and thinks of Romeo.

22
00:01:25,548 --> 00:01:31,092
"Oh Romeo, Romeo! Why are you a Montague?"

23
00:01:31,892 --> 00:01:35,852
"A rose by any other name is still sweet."

24
00:01:36,652 --> 00:01:41,044
Romeo says: "I love you, Juliet."

25
00:01:41,844 --> 00:01:46,140
Juliet says: "I love you, Romeo."

26
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:51,284
"But our families hate each other," says Juliet.

27
00:01:52,084 --> 00:01:58,228
"It doesn't matter," says Romeo. "Our love is stronger."

28
00:01:59,028 --> 00:02:03,108
The next day, they go to Friar Lawrence.

29
00:02:03,908 --> 00:02:07,460
Friar Lawrence marries them in secret.

30
00:02:08,260 --> 00:02:10,972
But then everything goes wrong.

31
00:02:11,772 --> 00:02:14,532
There is a fight in the street.

32
00:02:15,332 --> 00:02:18,260
Romeo's friend dies.

33
00:02:19,060 --> 00:02:22,084
Romeo is very angry.

34
00:02:22,884 --> 00:02:25,956
Romeo kills a Capulet.

35
00:02:26,756 --> 00:02:31,748
The prince says: "Romeo must leave Verona!"

36
00:02:32,548 --> 00:02:37,252
Romeo leaves. Juliet cries.

37
00:02:38,052 --> 00:02:43,212
Juliet's father says: "You must marry another man."

38
00:02:44,012 --> 00:02:48,500
Juliet says: "No! Never!"

39
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:52,252
Friar Lawrence has a plan.

40
00:02:53,052 --> 00:02:58,668
"Drink this medicine. You will sleep for two days."

41
00:02:59,468 --> 00:03:06,020
"Everyone thinks you are dead. Romeo comes and you wake up together."

42
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:09,892
Juliet drinks the medicine.

43
00:03:10,692 --> 00:03:15,132
She falls asleep. She looks dead.

44
00:03:15,932 --> 00:03:18,524
The family cries.

45
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:23,284
But Romeo does not receive the message about the plan.

46
00:03:24,084 --> 00:03:27,588
Romeo hears that Juliet is dead.

47
00:03:28,388 --> 00:03:33,428
"No! My Juliet!" shouts Romeo.

48
00:03:34,228 --> 00:03:37,012
Romeo returns to Verona.

49
00:03:37,812 --> 00:03:40,644
He goes to where Juliet sleeps.

50
00:03:41,444 --> 00:03:43,820
He thinks she is dead.

51
00:03:44,620 --> 00:03:48,772
"I cannot live without you," says Romeo.

52
00:03:49,572 --> 00:03:54,156
Romeo drinks the poison. He dies.

53
00:03:54,956 --> 00:03:57,596
Juliet wakes up.

54
00:03:58,396 --> 00:04:00,988
She sees Romeo dead.

55
00:04:01,788 --> 00:04:06,108
"No, no, no!" shouts Juliet.

56
00:04:06,908 --> 00:04:09,908
Juliet dies with Romeo.

57
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:13,684
The two families arrive.

58
00:04:14,484 --> 00:04:17,652
They see the two dead young people.

59
00:04:18,452 --> 00:04:20,948
They cry together.

60
00:04:21,748 --> 00:04:25,372
The Montagues and the Capulets make peace.

61
00:04:26,172 --> 00:04:29,244
But the price is too high.

62
00:04:30,044 --> 00:04:34,196
The love of Romeo and Juliet lives forever.
